text.tspan: Lung cancer death rate in men vs. women, 2022
The reported annual death rate from lung cancer per 100,000 people in men versus women, based on the
underlying cause listed on death certificates.
Data source: WHO Mortality Database (2024); Our World in Data
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, the metrics are age-standardized. All deaths in a country may not
have been registered with a cause of death.
